This paper deals with wireless communication technologies and interference management, which are typically studied in the computer science sub-category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The use of game theory and optimization theory also suggests a possible fit with the sub-category of Game Theory and Decision Science (cs.GT) and Information Theory (cs.IT). The proposed transmission policies also involve control and optimization, which could place the paper in the sub-categories of Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Multimedia (cs.MM).
